your cellphone. When you do so, you should see a numeric token. Please input it into the form below. If you selected the SMS option, you should have received this token in a text message.</span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Ahora, ingrese a la aplicaci&oacute;n que baj&oacute; a su celular. Al hacerlo, la aplicaci&oacute;n le mostrar&aacute; un c&oacute;digo, o &quot;token&quot; num&eacute;rico. Por favor ingr&eacute;selo en el formulario a continuaci&oacute;n. Si seleccion&oacute; la opci&oacute;n de recibirlo por SMS, el c&oacute;digo se le envi&oacute; como mensaje de texto.</span></p>\r\n','  ',' ','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">, &nbsp; 2FA,      &nbsp;.&nbsp;   , &nbsp;  .     .     SMS,     &nbsp;    .</span></p>\r\n','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),(32,'security-setup','Two-Factor Authentication Setup','Configuracin de autenticacin de dos factores','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Two-factor authentication is set up for your account using the following phone:</span></p>\r\n','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">La autenticaci&oacute;n de dos factores est&aacute; configurada para su cuenta usando el siguiente m&oacute;vil:</span></p>\r\n','  ','','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;,&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;:</span></p>\r\n','<p></p>\r\n'),(33,'security-token-login','Verify Your Token','Verificar su cdigo','<p>Please enter your token. This may be generated by the Authy App, Google Authenticator, or sent by SMS to your phone, depending on your preferences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please note: If you lost your phone you will need to go through our <a href=\"reset_2fa.php\" target=\"_blank\">reset process</a> to restore access.</p>\r\n','<p>Por favor ingrese el c&oacute;digo aleatorio. Este es generado por Authy, Google Authenticator, o recibido por SMS dependiendo de sus preferencias.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Por favor notar: Si se extravi&oacute; su tel&eacute;fono, tendr&aacute; que seguir nuestro <a href=\"es/reiniciar_2fa.php\" target=\"_blank\">proceso de recuperaci&oacute;n</a> para restaurar el acceso.</p>\r\n','  ',' ','<p><span style=\"font-size:12px;\">,   . &nbsp;  &nbsp;Authy App, Google Authenticator,    &nbsp;SMS  ,     .</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 20.7999992370605px;\">,  :   &nbsp;   &nbsp;  <a href=\"ru/-2fa.php\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></span></span><span style=\"line-height: 20.7999992370605px;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"line-height: 20.7999992370605px;\">2FA&nbsp;  .</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p>AuthyAuthenticator</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 20.7999992370605px;\"></span><a href=\"zh/.php\" target=\"_blank\"></a> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),(34,'what-are-bitcoins','A Short Introduction To Bitcoin','Una corta introduccin a los bitcoins','<h2>A Short Introduction to Bitcoin</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bitcoin</strong>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peer-to-peer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Peer-to-peer\">peer-to-peer</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Payment_system\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Payment system\">payment system</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_currency\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Digital currency\">digital currency</a>&nbsp;introduced as&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Open source\">open source</a>&nbsp;software in 2009 by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pseudonym\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Pseudonym\">pseudonymous</a>&nbsp;developer&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satoshi_Nakamoto\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Satoshi Nakamoto\">Satoshi Nakamoto</a>. It is a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptocurrency\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Cryptocurrency\">cryptocurrency</a>, so-called because it uses&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptography\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Cryptography\">cryptography</a>&nbsp;to control the creation and transfer of money. Users send payments by broadcasting&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_signature\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Digital signature\">digitally signed</a>&nbsp;messages to the network. Participants known as&nbsp;<a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin_mining\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Bitcoin mining\">miners</a>&nbsp;verify and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timestamp\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Timestamp\">timestamp</a>&nbsp;transactions into a shared public database called the block chain, for which they are rewarded with transaction fees and newly minted bitcoins. Conventionally &quot;Bitcoin&quot; capitalized refers to the technology and network whereas &quot;bitcoins&quot; lowercase refers to the currency itself.&nbsp;Bitcoins can be obtained by mining or in exchange for products, services, or other currencies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Source: Wikipedia</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Gc2en3nHxA4\" width=\"560\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<h2>Una corta introducci&oacute;n sobre Bitcoin</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bitc&oacute;in</strong> (signo: ; abr.: BTC) es una <a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Criptodivisa\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Criptodivisa\">criptodivisa</a> descentralizada concebida en <a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/2008\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"2008\">2008</a> por una persona (o grupo de personas) que bajo el seud&oacute;nimo &quot;<a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin#Satoshi_Nakamoto\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Bitcoin\">Satoshi Nakamoto</a>&quot; public&oacute; un libro blanco que propone un sistema de transacciones electr&oacute;nicas que no depende de la confianza, sino que permite realizar transferencias de forma directa sin la necesidad de un intermediario. El t&eacute;rmino se aplica tambi&eacute;n al <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protocolo_%28inform%C3%A1tica%29\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Protocolo (informtica)\">protocolo</a> dise&ntilde;ado por el mismo autor y a la <a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_de_computadoras\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Red de computadoras\">red</a> <a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peer-to-peer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Peer-to-peer\">P2P</a> que lo sustenta. Al contrario de la mayor&iacute;a de las monedas, el bitc&oacute;in no est&aacute; respaldado por ning&uacute;n gobierno ni depende de la confianza en ning&uacute;n emisor central, sino que utiliza un <a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proof-of-work_system\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Proof-of-work system\">sistema de prueba de trabajo</a> para impedir el doble gasto y alcanzar el consenso entre todos los nodos que integran la red. Bitcoin es un proyecto relativamente nuevo que se encuentra en evoluci&oacute;n. Por esta raz&oacute;n, sus desarrolladores recomiendan ser cautos y tratarlo como software experimental.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Source: Wikipedia</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Gc2en3nHxA4\" width=\"560\"></iframe></p>\r\n','   ',' ','<h2>   </h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px;\">- <u><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peer-to-peer\" target=\"_blank\">() </a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Payment_system\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></u>  <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_currency\" target=\"_blank\"><u> </u></a>,      <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source\" target=\"_blank\"><u>  </u></a>  2009    <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pseudonym\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satoshi_Nakamoto\" target=\"_blank\"><u> </u></a>. -<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptocurrency\" target=\"_blank\"></a>,  ,    <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptography\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a>      .       ,  <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_signature\" target=\"_blank\"><u> </u></a>. ,   <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin_mining\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a>,    <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timestamp\" target=\"_blank\"><u> </u></a>      ( )     &quot; &quot;.             . -   ,     ,     .           .           , ,    .</span></p>\r\n','<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n (: ;Bitcoin;: BTC)<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peer-to-peer\" target=\"_blank\">P2P</a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_currency\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satoshi_Nakamoto\" target=\"_blank\"></a>Satoshi Nakamoto2009 <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptocurrency\" target=\"_blank\"></a>Cryptocurrency<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptography\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_signature\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin_mining\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timestamp\" target=\"_blank\"></a>Bitcoinbitcoin </p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),(35,'how-bitcoin-works','How Does Bitcoin Work?','Cmo funciona Bitcoin?','<h1>How does <strong>Bitcoin</strong> work?</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a question that often causes confusion. Here&#39;s a quick explanation!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>The basics for a new user</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">As a new user, you can&nbsp;get started&nbsp;with Bitcoin without understanding the technical details. Once you have installed a Bitcoin wallet on your computer or mobile phone, it will generate your first Bitcoin address and you can create more whenever you need one. You can disclose your addresses to your friends so that they can pay you or vice versa. In fact, this is pretty similar to how email works, except that Bitcoin addresses should only be used once.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Balances&nbsp;- block chain</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The block chain is a&nbsp;<strong>shared public ledger</strong>&nbsp;on which the entire Bitcoin network relies. All confirmed transactions are included in the block chain. This way, Bitcoin wallets can calculate their spendable balance and new transactions can be verified to be spending bitcoins that are actually owned by the spender. The integrity and the chronological order of the block chain are enforced with&nbsp;cryptography.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Transactions&nbsp;- private keys</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A transaction is&nbsp;<strong>a transfer of value between Bitcoin wallets</strong>&nbsp;that gets included in the block chain. Bitcoin wallets keep a secret piece of data called a&nbsp;<em>private key</em>&nbsp;or seed, which is used to sign transactions, providing a mathematical proof that they have come from the owner of the wallet. The&nbsp;<em>signature</em>&nbsp;also prevents the transaction from being altered by anybody once it has been issued. All transactions are broadcast between users and usually begin to be confirmed by the network in the following 10 minutes, through a process called&nbsp;<em>mining</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Processing&nbsp;- mining</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Mining is a&nbsp;<strong>distributed consensus system</strong>&nbsp;that is used to&nbsp;<em>confirm</em>&nbsp;waiting transactions by including them in the block chain. It enforces a chronological order in the block chain, protects the neutrality of the network, and allows different computers to agree on the state of the system. To be confirmed, transactions must be packed in a&nbsp;<em>block</em>&nbsp;that fits very strict cryptographic rules that will be verified by the network. These rules prevent previous blocks from being modified because doing so would invalidate all following blocks. Mining also creates the equivalent of a competitive lottery that prevents any individual from easily adding new blocks consecutively in the block chain. This way, no individuals can control what is included in the block chain or replace parts of the block chain to roll back their own spends.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Going down the rabbit hole</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This is only a very short and concise summary of the system. If you want to get into the details, you can&nbsp;<a href=\"https://bitcoin.org/bitcoin.pdf\" style=\"color: rgb(44, 111, 173); text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">read the original paper</a>&nbsp;that describes the system&#39;s design, and explore the&nbsp;Bitcoin wiki.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em>Source:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.bitcoin.org\" target=\"_blank\"> &quot;www.bitcoin.org&quot;</a></em></p>\r\n','<h1>&iquest;C&oacute;mo funciona <strong>Bitcoin</strong>?</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Esta es una pregunta que a menudo causa confusiones. &iexcl;Aqu&iacute; tiene una explicaci&oacute;n r&aacute;pida!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Lo esencial para un usuario nuevo</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Como usuario nuevo, usted puede&nbsp;empezar&nbsp;con Bitcoin sin entender los detalles t&eacute;cnicos. Una vez usted tenga instalado un monedero en su ordenador o dispositivo m&oacute;vil, se generar&aacute; su primera direcci&oacute;n Bitcoin y podr&aacute; crear m&aacute;s cuando lo necesite. Puede dar su direcci&oacute;n a sus amigos para que le paguen o viceversa. De hecho, es similar a como funciona el correo electr&oacute;nico, excepto que las direcciones Bitcoin solamente deber&iacute;an ser usadas una &uacute;nica vez.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Balances&nbsp;- cadena de bloques</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">La cadena de bloques o &quot;block chain&quot; es una&nbsp;<strong>contabilidad p&uacute;blica compartida</strong>&nbsp;en la que se basa toda la red Bitcoin. Todas las transacciones confirmadas se incluyen en la cadena de bloques. De esta manera los monederos Bitcoin pueden calcular su saldo gastable y las nuevas transacciones pueden ser verificadas, asegurando que el cobro se esta haciendo al que realiza el pago. La integridad y el orden cronol&oacute;gico de la cadena de bloques se hacen cumplir concriptograf&iacute;a.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Transacciones&nbsp;- llaves privadas</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Una transacci&oacute;n es&nbsp;<strong>una transferencia de valores entre monederos Bitcoin</strong>&nbsp;que ser&aacute; incluida en la cadena de bloques. Los monederos Bitcoin disponen de un fragmento secreto llamado&nbsp;clave privada, utilizada para firmar las operaciones, proporcionando una prueba matem&aacute;tica de que la transacci&oacute;n est&aacute; hecha por el propietario del monedero. La&nbsp;firma&nbsp;tambi&eacute;n evita que la transacci&oacute;n no sea alterada por alguien una vez &eacute;sta ha sido emitida. Todas las transacciones son difundidas entre los usuarios y por lo general empiezan a ser confirmadas por la red en los 10 minutos siguientes a trav&eacute;s de un proceso llamado&nbsp;miner&iacute;a.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Procesamiento&nbsp;- miner&iacute;a</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">La miner&iacute;a es un&nbsp;<strong>sistema de consenso distribuido</strong>&nbsp;que se utiliza para&nbsp;confirmar&nbsp;las transacciones pendientes a ser incluidas en la cadena de bloques. Hace cumplir un orden cronol&oacute;gico en la cadena de bloques, protege la neutralidad de la red y permite un acuerde entre todos los equipos sobre el estado del sistema. Para confirmar las transacciones, deber&aacute;n ser empacadas en un&nbsp;bloque&nbsp;que se ajuste a estrictas normas de cifrado y que ser&aacute; verificado por la red. Estas normas impiden que cualquier bloque anterior se modifique, ya que hacerlo invalidar&iacute;a todos los bloques siguientes. La miner&iacute;a tambi&eacute;n crea el equivalente a una loter&iacute;a competitiva que impide que cualquier persona pueda f&aacute;cilmente a&ntilde;adir nuevos bloques consecutivamente en la cadena de bloques. De esta manera, ninguna persona puede controlar lo que est&aacute; incluido en la cadena de bloques o reemplazar partes de la cadena de bloques para revertir sus propios gastos.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&iquest;Hasta qu&eacute; punto est&aacute;s dispuesto a descubrir m&aacute;s?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Esto es s&oacute;lo un resumen muy breve y conciso del sistema. Si quieres conocer mas los detalles, puedes leer el&nbsp;<a href=\"https://bitcoin.org/bitcoin_es_latam.pdf\" style=\"color: rgb(44, 111, 173); text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">art&iacute;culo original</a>&nbsp;que describe el dise&ntilde;o del sistema, y explorar el&nbsp;Wiki de Bitcoin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em>Source: <a href=\"http://www.bitcoin.org/es\" target=\"_blank\">&quot;www.bitcoin.org&quot;</a></em></p>\r\n','  ','','<p><!--?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?--></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-size:22px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">   ?</span></span></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"></span><!--?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?--></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>     .   !</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!--?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?--></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<h3><strong><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">   </span></span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>  ,   <em> </em>  ,     .     -      ,     - ,        ,  .      ,     ,  .   ,         ,   ,  -     .</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!--?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?--></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<h3><strong><